        <briefdescription>
<para>Apply power state constraints by locking the specified states. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function locks all power states specified in the union of all constraints in the provided constraint list. Each constraint in the set contributes to determining which power states should be locked (not allowed), by increasing a reference count just as if pm_policy_state_lock_get was called on each constraints&apos; states individually.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>constraints</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the power state constraints set to apply.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
