        <briefdescription>
<para>Remove power state constraints by unlocking the specified states. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function unlocks all power states that were previously locked by a corresponding call to <ref refid="group__subsys__pm__sys__policy_1ga43ad016f054543cf96c2362ccf12d29a" kindref="member">pm_policy_state_constraints_get()</ref> with the same constraint set. The function decreases the lock counter for each affected power state specified in the union of all constraints in the list, just as if pm_policy_state_put was called on all the constraints&apos; states individually.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>constraints</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the power state constraints set to remove.</para>
